      • getFileContents

        String getFileContents(File root,
                     String... fileNames)
                       throws FileNotFoundException,
                              IOException
        Retrieve the contents of a file relative to the root file.

        The process should look for the first file from fileNames that it can find and return that contents.

        Parameters:
        root - The root file.
        fileNames - The file names relative to the root file.
        Returns:
        The contents of the first file found.
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException - If none of the files exist.
        IOException - If there is a problem reading any of the files.
